# JavaFX Instruction

**Java FX Link**
Link: https://gluonhq.com/products/javafx/

Steps:
  1. Download JavaFX SDK
  2. Create java project
  3. Add SDK library
    a. File
    b. Project structure
    c. Libraries
    d. Select javafx library (lib)
    e. Select OK -> OK -> Apply
  4. Add VM Options
    a. Run
    b. Edit Configurations...
    c. Next to VM options enter the command:
      Linux/Mac: --module-path /path/to/javafx-sdk-15.0.1/lib --add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml
      Windows: --module-path "\path\to\javafx-sdk-15.0.1\lib" --add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml
    
**Source**
IntelliJ: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ope4icw6bVk&t=7s
Eclipse:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_7OM-cMYWbQ&t=155s
